      "content": "Okay, I see. So it's more about the scope of what I'm responsible for. \n\nYou mentioned these \"sneaky traps\" and \"hidden\" damages. It sounds like things that could just pop up out of nowhere and ruin everything. Are there any other ways these clauses can be written to be \"predatory\" or \"sneaky\"? Like, how do they hide these things so you don't notice them until it's too late?",
